## 📐 PAGE STRUCTURE REQUIREMENTS

### **Each Product Page Must Include (Top to Bottom):**

1. **Breadcrumbs**
   - Home > Shop > [Category] > [Product Name]
   - With proper schema markup

2. **Product Section** (Hero Area)
   - Product image (left on desktop, top on mobile)
   - Product details (right on desktop, below on mobile):
     - H1 with product name
     - Price (current + original if on sale)
     - Rating stars
     - Stock status
     - Feature badges (NEW, TRENDING, % OFF)
     - CTA button linking to affiliate URL
     - Trust signals

3. **Product Description Section**
   - 400-word unique, semantically optimized description
   - Written specifically for each product
   - Includes semantic keywords naturally
   - Engaging and conversion-focused

4. **Specifications Section** (Optional but Recommended)
   - Key product specs in structured format
   - Package contents
   - Material details
   - Application time
   - Durability

5. **Internal Links Section - Related Products**
   - 5 related products from same category
   - Displayed as cards in a row
   - Responsive grid layout

6. **Internal Links Section - Related Categories**
   - 3 related shop categories
   - Card-based layout with images

7. **Internal Links Section - Cross-Page Links**
   - 1 related blog post
   - 1 related inspo (nail design)
   - 1 related topic page
   - Displayed as 3 cards in a row

8. **FAQ Section** (if applicable)
   - Product-specific FAQs
   - With FAQ schema markup

